“I think that focusing on the importance of #mentalhealth is  my calling,” said our April cover star, #DeepikaPadukone. In 2015, the #Bollywood actor made headlines after sharing her struggle with #depression. As Padukone reports, in India, there’s still considerable stigma around discussing mental health, which prompted her to speak out.

With box office hits, a flourishing relationship (with now-husband @ranveersingh), and lucrative ad campaigns, it would have seemed to any outsider that Padukone was on top of the world. But, she didn’t feel that way, grappling with her depression in silence until her mother intervened. “I struggled and I suffered for many months because I didn’t know anyone who had been through something like this,” she said. “I felt if I shared my experience and even just one person was like, ‘I identify with these symptoms,’ then my purpose would be served.” Enter the Live Love Laugh Foundation. 

In 2015, Padukone established @tlllfoundation to keep the conversation going and to provide resources for those who are suffering. “It’s work that I will continue to do. And hopefully the foundation will survive even beyond me,” said Padukone.

Read her full interview with @diannamazzone at the #linkinbio.

‘What’s your legacy?’ is a daunting question. But, at just 36, actress #DeepikaPadukone, has been thinking about it a lot lately. “You reach a stage in your life where you wake up thinking, what is it that I want to be remembered for?,” the #Bollywood star told us in her April cover interview. 

The answer — in addition to her #mentalhealth foundation and impressive acting credits — is a lifestyle brand. Centered on self-care and ritual, the star has big plans for her soon-to-be-named brand, with five skin care products currently in the works. Mental health is a cause that is extremely personal and dear to me. Over the last 5 years, donors, partners, government authorities and our incredible team have all played a crucial role in LiveLoveLaugh’s journey, but the greatest impact has been from those who have had a lived experience with mental illness, and their caregivers. I would like to see a world where no life is lost due to mental illness, and LiveLoveLaugh is committed to delivering on that aspiration.
______
Posted @withregram • @tlllfoundation We are delighted to launch our new brand identity. When we started five years ago, we knew we wanted to transform the mental health conversation in India. There’s so much more to do, but the progress we see has been heartening. Our journey has been anchored in our mission to give hope to every person experiencing stress, anxiety, and depression.
We believe that hope can be at the heart of our mental health, and fittingly, hope finds itself at the centre of our new brand identity. From the warm hues of the colour palette to the accessible typeface, the LiveLoveLaugh brand emphasizes inclusivity, compassion, and hope. Explore the fresh look at our new website. Link in the bio.
